{{!-- ── GUIDE STEPS ─────────────────────────────────────────────── --}}
<div class="rm-onboard-steps">

  {{!-- STEP 1: Equipment --}}
  <section class="rm-onboard-step" id="step-1">
    <div class="rm-onboard-step__inner">
      <div class="rm-onboard-step__meta">
        <span class="rm-onboard-step__num">01</span>
        <span class="rm-onboard-step__tag">Foundation</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-onboard-step__body">
        <h2 class="rm-onboard-step__title">Gear Up — Managing your equipment</h2>
        <a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360014710799-Explore-Our-Plans" class="rm-onboard-plan-badge" target="_blank" rel="noopener">📦 Equipment Scheduling</a>
        <p class="rm-onboard-step__desc">The secret to a smooth experience starts with how you organise your warehouse virtually. Get your gear into the system the right way from day one.</p>
        <div class="rm-onboard-step__tip">
          <span class="rm-onboard-step__tip-label">💡 Best practice</span>
          <p>Use <strong>Physical Combinations</strong> for permanently bundled items (like a rack-mounted amp). Use <strong>Virtual Combinations</strong> for items often rented together but separable. Your warehouse team will always know exactly what to pack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rm-onboard-step__resources">
          <div class="rm-onboard-step__articles">
            <p class="rm-onboard-step__res-label">📄 Articles</p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360014141299-Import-Your-Equipment">Import your Equipment via Excel/CSV</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360013703140-Create-Equipment-Combinations">Create Equipment Combinations</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/4402870209682-Equipment-Combinations-and-How-to-Work-with-Them">Equipment Combinations and How to Work with Them</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rm-onboard-step__video">
            <p class="rm-onboard-step__res-label">🎬 Watch on demand</p>
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fm_bmQDHPew" class="rm-onboard-video-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <span class="rm-onboard-video-link__play" aria-hidden="true">▶</span>
              How to import your equipment into Rentman
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {{!-- STEP 2: Crew (was step 5) --}}
  <section class="rm-onboard-step rm-onboard-step--alt" id="step-2">
    <div class="rm-onboard-step__inner">
      <div class="rm-onboard-step__meta">
        <span class="rm-onboard-step__num">02</span>
        <span class="rm-onboard-step__tag">People</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-onboard-step__body">
        <h2 class="rm-onboard-step__title">The Human Element — Mastering crew scheduling</h2>
        <a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360014710799-Explore-Our-Plans" class="rm-onboard-plan-badge" target="_blank" rel="noopener">👥 Crew Scheduling</a>
        <p class="rm-onboard-step__desc">Your crew are central to everything you do. Get them into the system early — before you start planning projects — so you're ready to assign the right people from day one.</p>
        <div class="rm-onboard-step__tip">
          <span class="rm-onboard-step__tip-label">💡 Best practice</span>
          <p>Tag crew members with skills and certifications (like <strong>#LeadTech</strong>, <strong>#A1</strong>, <strong>#TruckDriver</strong>) in their profiles. Filter by tag when planning to instantly see the most qualified people — no scrolling through your entire database.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rm-onboard-step__resources">
          <div class="rm-onboard-step__articles">
            <p class="rm-onboard-step__res-label">📄 Articles</p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/14232209807506-Functions-What-are-they-and-how-to-create-them">Setting up Functions</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360014610140-Crew-Planner-Module">Using the Crew Planner</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360014672919-Communicate-the-Crew-Planning">Communicating the Crew Planning</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rm-onboard-step__video">
            <p class="rm-onboard-step__res-label">🎬 Watch on demand</p>
            <a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360015581499-Video-Introduction-to-planning-your-crew-and-transport" class="rm-onboard-video-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <span class="rm-onboard-video-link__play" aria-hidden="true">▶</span>
              Introduction to planning your crew and transport
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {{!-- STEP 3: Projects (was step 2) --}}
  <section class="rm-onboard-step" id="step-3">
    <div class="rm-onboard-step__inner">
      <div class="rm-onboard-step__meta">
        <span class="rm-onboard-step__num">03</span>
        <span class="rm-onboard-step__tag">Planning</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-onboard-step__body">
        <h2 class="rm-onboard-step__title">From Zero to Booked — Planning your first project</h2>
        <a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360014710799-Explore-Our-Plans" class="rm-onboard-plan-badge" target="_blank" rel="noopener">🔧 Rentman Platform</a>
        <p class="rm-onboard-step__desc">Now that your gear is in the system, it's time to move from inventory to action. Build your first project and stop starting from scratch every time.</p>
        <div class="rm-onboard-step__tip">
          <span class="rm-onboard-step__tip-label">💡 Best practice</span>
          <p>Always set your <strong>Planning period</strong> slightly longer than your <strong>Usage period</strong> to account for prep and load-out. This prevents ghost shortages where gear looks available but is still on a truck.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rm-onboard-step__resources">
          <div class="rm-onboard-step__articles">
            <p class="rm-onboard-step__res-label">📄 Articles</p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360013367659-Project-Templates">Using Project Templates</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360017700339-What-are-planning-and-usage-periods">Planning vs. Usage periods explained</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360013730520-Plan-Equipment-on-a-Project">Planning equipment and crew on a project</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rm-onboard-step__video">
            <p class="rm-onboard-step__res-label">🎬 Watch on demand</p>
            <a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360015575940-Video-Introduction-to-creating-managing-your-projects" class="rm-onboard-video-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <span class="rm-onboard-video-link__play" aria-hidden="true">▶</span>
              Introduction to creating &amp; managing your projects
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {{!-- STEP 4: Quotes & Invoicing (was step 3) --}}
  <section class="rm-onboard-step rm-onboard-step--alt" id="step-4">
    <div class="rm-onboard-step__inner">
      <div class="rm-onboard-step__meta">
        <span class="rm-onboard-step__num">04</span>
        <span class="rm-onboard-step__tag">Financials</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-onboard-step__body">
        <h2 class="rm-onboard-step__title">The Money Talk — Quotes and invoices simplified</h2>
        <a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360014710799-Explore-Our-Plans" class="rm-onboard-plan-badge rm-onboard-plan-badge--addon" target="_blank" rel="noopener">➕ Quoting &amp; Invoicing add-on required</a>
        <p class="rm-onboard-step__desc">Turn your hard work into revenue. Make sure your client-facing documents look as professional as your events — from first quote to final invoice.</p>
        <div class="rm-onboard-step__tip">
          <span class="rm-onboard-step__tip-label">💡 Best practice</span>
          <p>Use Rentman's task system to set a reminder to follow up on unsigned quotes after 3 days. A gentle nudge often makes the difference between a "maybe" and a "confirmed".</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rm-onboard-step__resources">
          <div class="rm-onboard-step__articles">
            <p class="rm-onboard-step__res-label">📄 Articles</p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360013503420-Document-Templates">Using the Document Template Editor</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360012594659-Create-a-Quotation-or-a-Contract">Create a Quotation or Contract</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360017648580-How-do-I-generate-invoices-in-Rentman">Invoicing your Client</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rm-onboard-step__video">
            <p class="rm-onboard-step__res-label">🎬 Watch on demand</p>
            <a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360015729040-Video-Introduction-to-Financials" class="rm-onboard-video-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <span class="rm-onboard-video-link__play" aria-hidden="true">▶</span>
              Introduction to Financials
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {{!-- STEP 5: Logistics (was step 4) --}}
  <section class="rm-onboard-step" id="step-5">
    <div class="rm-onboard-step__inner">
      <div class="rm-onboard-step__meta">
        <span class="rm-onboard-step__num">05</span>
        <span class="rm-onboard-step__tag">Logistics</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-onboard-step__body">
        <h2 class="rm-onboard-step__title">Logistics Masterclass — Managing shortages and returns</h2>
        <a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360014710799-Explore-Our-Plans" class="rm-onboard-plan-badge rm-onboard-plan-badge--addon" target="_blank" rel="noopener">➕ Equipment Tracking add-on required</a>
        <p class="rm-onboard-step__desc">Equipment needs to be in two places at once and things don't always come back on time. Here's how Rentman helps you handle those moments before they become problems.</p>
        <div class="rm-onboard-step__tip">
          <span class="rm-onboard-step__tip-label">💡 Best practice</span>
          <p>A red line in your timeline isn't a failure — it's a prompt. Use the <strong>Quick Subrental</strong> feature directly from the shortage view to track costs and prevent double-booking in seconds.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rm-onboard-step__resources">
          <div class="rm-onboard-step__articles">
            <p class="rm-onboard-step__res-label">📄 Articles</p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360013771040-Solve-Equipment-Shortages-with-Subrentals">Solve Equipment Shortages with Subrentals</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/13901986840082-Manually-Book-Equipment">The Equipment Return Process</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/17531415206418-How-to-Handle-Lost-or-Defective-Equipment-in-the-Warehouse">Handling lost or defective equipment</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rm-onboard-step__video">
            <p class="rm-onboard-step__res-label">🎬 Watch on demand</p>
            <a href="https://support.rentman.io/hc/en-us/articles/360015577120-Video-Introduction-into-planning-and-tracking-your-equipment" class="rm-onboard-video-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <span class="rm-onboard-video-link__play" aria-hidden="true">▶</span>
              Introduction to planning and tracking your equipment
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</div>
